this joke based on fact that in German "Ja" (Yes) sounds just like russian "Я" (I (am/did/was/e.t.c)).

here is fun fact. It might looks like joke but i am serious. In russian language many "difficult" words such as technical definitions, science or engeneering definitions came from english "usual" (simple) words. So when some "smart" guy uses smart "russian" word, often all i need is eng2rus dictionary, not explanatory dictionary.
